Mechanic App
Description
This project models a workplace with different types of employees (Mechanic, Worker, Manager, TeamLead, etc.) and vehicles.
It demonstrates Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts in Java such as:
•	Classes and objects
•	Inheritance
•	Encapsulation (getters/setters)
•	Polymorphism
The source files provided are:
•	MechanicApp.java (main program)
•	Vehicle.java
•	Vehicleclass.java
•	Employee.java
•	Worker.java
•	Manager.java
•	TeamLead.java
Requirements
•	Java Development Kit (JDK) 17 or higher
•	IntelliJ IDEA (Community or Ultimate)
Running in IntelliJ IDEA
1.	Open IntelliJ IDEA
o	Go to File > New > Project from Existing Sources...
o	Select the folder where these .java files are located.
2.	Set up JDK
o	When prompted, select your installed Java SDK (17 or higher).
3.	Mark source folder
o	Right-click the folder with your .java files > Mark Directory as > Sources Root.
4.	Run the program
o	Open MechanicApp.java.
